name: So_Bubbles
description:
The simple completion of a strict form with casually different dimensions and its intense transparency. 

Only when/where they rest on a plane, so_bubbles lose their perfect round shape to bind to the reality of a piece of furniture with the sharpness and lightness of the glass, thus already foreseeing the likelihood to move again looking for a new contamination, in an original choreography brightened up by light or animated by movement, in a surprising game of reflected signs and cross-references between what is suspended inside them and the place where they are.

Material: glass and cork base
Dimension: diameter 8cm + 10cm + 12 cm
Weight: 150 gr

name: Paccheri family
description:
Through the use of porcelain, a material that tells a long and lasting habit about commu- nion and diversity, my project celebrates the symbolic and traditional Italian cuisine. The porcelain brings inside an imaginary of elegant and sophistication, research for details and fine workmanship, which binds perfectly to the culture of pasta that is carefully crafted and respect for tradition. What is hidden behind the simple shape of pasta are centuries refinement of a tradition that links its roots in a land full of history and culture. The study of the shape, in its elegance and simplicity, brings in the domestic space the act of pouring pasta, through the iconic and symbolic elements; methodically designed to attend the function. The object becomes a celebration of its content. The porcelain, like pasta, is a historical and deep-rooted tradition. This is why compare the two main elements, pasta and porcelain, seem to complement each other.

Details;
Object size 290X115 , 312X55 mm 
Packaging size 90X90X 330 mm 
Shipping Size 150X150X350 mm
Weight around 1 Kg
Materials Porcelain Cork

Realized incollaboration with Capodimonte Porcellane dʼArte 
www.ca- podimonteporcellanedarte.com

name: Connection
description:
Connection is a furniture system composed by only two components, a plexglass part fixed to the wall in a triangular shape, and a
circular hook that allows the union between the parties, creating networks and connections endless.
It’s a functional wall that pulls in objects;
scarves, hats, umbrellas, keys, bags, this components create network conformations always new and interesting.
A hanger that becomes a game, never losing its elegance and its decorative presence in a living area.
Each user can, in fact, thanks to a connection, create freely different conformations; conformations suitable on their own space requirements.
The user have exclusively the instruments, and a few constraints for construction of the object. For the rest, everyone will feel free to
propose its shape, different from that of other users.
The system connection is provided here. It represents a project really suitable for everyone and all needs without exception.

Kit of 5 pieces

Available in 5/7 days

name: Nests

A smart space saving system of soft containers made in different shapes and tactile materials. Designed to be used at home to organize books, DVDs, food packages, etc.  The Nests can be hung in two different ways: on shelves or on the wall via a dedicated kit of hooks.   The first one helps to duplicate the space of your shelves and free up your desk, the other is an alternative storage system that enhances your wall space.   An Inclusive design, tactile containers allowing blind or visually impaired to easily move and recognize any kind of object through touch.

name: Matawi
description:
Matawi means branches in Swahili.
In Africa the tree is the principle of life itself that collects knowledge and is "the object" around which organizes and develops daily life.
The structural matrix of the library Matawi is inspired by its beauty, the strength and simplicity of the sign generated from the branches of African's tree.
The shape and the joints of the module make that the library Matawi may ramify endlessly generating the most varied compositions.

name: Crop up
description:
CROP UP is a suspended pot for both indoors and outdoors. 
It frees the surfaces (floors and furnitures) establishing a diaphanous relationship with its environment. 
Its image, apparently fragile and unsteady, leads to courteous approaches, slows times of fruition, causes expectation and coax reflection. 
The porosity of non lacquered ceramic of its watering-cup exploits its materials features, to interpretate new parameters between form and function.
